---
// Main content for marketplace/wallawhats page
---

<div class="container-medium container-solution">
  <div class="solution-page-card">
    <div class="solution-page-content-wrapper">
      <div class="integration-content-copy">
        <div class="top-content integration-card-top-content">
          <div class="split-solution-header">
            <div class="image-wrapper integration-icon-wrapper">
              <div class="wallawhats-icon-badge" role="img" aria-label="WallaWhats">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-dove" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="split-content integration-details">
              <div class="integration-title-wrapper">
                <h1 class="title h2-size integration-name">WallaWhats</h1>
              </div>
              <p class="paragraph integration-about-excerpt">
                WallaWhats turns any X/Twitter account into a WhatsApp feed. Pick the handles you want to follow, verify
                your WhatsApp number, and new posts arrive as WhatsApp messages — typically in under ten seconds. No app
                install, no extra dashboard to check, no missed drops.
              </p>
              <div class="split-button-solution">
                <div class="split-first-buttons-solution">
                  <div class="solution-links">
                    <a
                      href="https://wallawhats.com"
                      target="_blank"
                      rel="noopener noreferrer"
                      class="button-primary small flex landing-page-link-button w-inline-block"
                      ><div class="text-block-24">Open WallaWhats</div>
                      &nbsp;<i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></a
                    >
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="collection-list-wrapper w-dyn-list" style="margin-left: auto;">
                  <div class="empty-state-3 w-dyn-empty"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="split-content integration-card-content">
          <div
            data-duration-in="300"
            data-duration-out="100"
            data-current="Description"
            data-easing="ease"
            class="integration-tabs w-tabs"
          >
            <div class="integration-tabs-menu w-tab-menu">
              <a data-w-tab="Description" class="integration-tab-link w-inline-block w-tab-link w--current"
                ><div>Description</div></a
              ><a data-w-tab="Integration" class="integration-tab-link last w-inline-block w-tab-link"
                ><div>Integration</div></a
              >
            </div>
            <div class="integrations-tabs-content w-tab-content">
              <div data-w-tab="Description" class="integration-tab w-tab-pane w--tab-active">
                <div class="rich-text w-richtext">
                  <p>
                    <strong>WallaWhats</strong> is the simplest way to get real-time WhatsApp alerts when the X (Twitter)
                    accounts you care about publish a new post. Pick the handles, verify your WhatsApp number, and
                    tweets reach your phone as WhatsApp messages — typically within seconds of being posted. It works on
                    iOS and Android with your existing WhatsApp account, and exposes a REST API so you can plug alerts
                    into your own applications and workflows.
                  </p>
                  <h4><strong>Features</strong></h4>
                  <h5><strong>Real-Time Delivery</strong></h5>
                  <p>Tweets from monitored accounts reach WhatsApp within seconds of going live on X/Twitter.</p>
                  <h5><strong>Multi-Account Monitoring</strong></h5>
                  <p>Follow any public X/Twitter handle. Add or remove accounts at any time from a single dashboard.</p>
                  <h5><strong>No App Required</strong></h5>
                  <p>
                    Uses the WhatsApp number you already have, on iOS or Android. Nothing to install, nothing new to
                    learn.
                  </p>
                  <h5><strong>Delivery Status History</strong></h5>
                  <p>
                    Every alert is logged with full delivery status — queued, sent, delivered, read, or failed — so you
                    always know what reached which number.
                  </p>
                  <h5><strong>REST API</strong></h5>
                  <p>
                    Manage monitored accounts, configure alerts, and pull notification history directly from your own
                    backend.
                  </p>
                  <h4><strong>Benefits</strong></h4>
                  <h5><strong>Never Miss a Drop</strong></h5>
                  <p>
                    Creator announcements, sponsor partnerships, and product reveals surface where you actually see
                    them — not buried in a timeline.
                  </p>
                  <h5><strong>Trade and React Faster</strong></h5>
                  <p>
                    Market-moving posts from traders or analysts hit your phone the moment they&#x27;re published, so
                    you never lose ground to latency.
                  </p>
                  <h5><strong>Protect Your Brand</strong></h5>
                  <p>
                    Monitor competitors and mentions without needing a social-listening team on standby. One tool,
                    one channel, one alert stream.
                  </p>
                  <h5><strong>One Channel for Signal</strong></h5>
                  <p>
                    Instead of a noisy timeline, WhatsApp becomes a filtered feed of only the accounts that matter to
                    you.
                  </p>
                  <p>‍</p>
                  <p>
                    Start monitoring for free at <a
                      href="https://wallawhats.com"
                      target="_blank"
                      rel="noopener noreferrer">wallawhats.com</a
                    >. Verify your WhatsApp number, pick a handle, and your next tweet becomes a WhatsApp message.
                  </p>
                  <p>‍</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div data-w-tab="Integration" class="integration-tab w-tab-pane">
                <div class="rich-text w-richtext">
                  <h4><strong>REST API</strong></h4>
                  <p>
                    WallaWhats exposes a REST API at <code>api.wallawhats.com</code>, secured by an
                    <code>x-api-key</code> header. You can manage monitored accounts, register and verify phone numbers,
                    pull notification history, and rotate keys — all from your own application. Rate limits are
                    generous (20 req/sec per key, with bursting) and the API uses cursor-based pagination so you can
                    stream full histories without paging offsets.
                  </p>
                  <h4><strong>Common integration patterns</strong></h4>
                  <ul role="list">
                    <li>Route WallaWhats alerts into a trading desk, a content pipeline, or an on-call rotation.</li>
                    <li>Centralize brand mentions across a team by subscribing one phone to the shared handles.</li>
                    <li>
                      Trigger downstream workflows (webhooks, analytics writes, internal bots) when specific accounts
                      post.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    Full reference: <a
                      href="https://wallawhats.com/docs/api-reference"
                      target="_blank"
                      rel="noopener noreferrer">wallawhats.com/docs/api-reference</a
                    >.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="inline integration-card">
            <a
              href="https://wallawhats.com"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="button-primary small flex w-inline-block"
              ><div>Get Started Free</div>
              &nbsp;<i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-up-right-from-square"></i></a
            >
            <a
              href="/contact-us.html?solution=wallawhats"
              class="button-secondary small flex w-inline-block"
              ><div>Contact Sales</div></a
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style is:global>
  .wallawhats-icon-badge {
    width: 110px;
    height: 110px;
    border-radius: 22px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #25D366 0%, #1a1b1e 100%);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 26px rgba(17, 17, 17, 0.12);
  }

  .wallawhats-icon-badge > i {
    color: #ffffff;
    font-size: 52px;
    line-height: 1;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25));
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 767px) {
    .wallawhats-icon-badge {
      width: 88px;
      height: 88px;
      border-radius: 18px;
    }
    .wallawhats-icon-badge > i {
      font-size: 40px;
    }
  }
</style>
